instructions:
1. Tenderize and cube the flank steak
  2. Add the cubed flank steak to a mixing bowl. Coat with salt, pepper to taste and coat with 1-2 tablespoons of olive oil
  3. Prepare the sauce by combining the coconut aminos, bone broth, sesame oil, garlic, ginger, monk fruit sweetener, pepper and lime
  4. Heat up a large pan on medium heat and add the steak
  5. Cook 2-3 minutes on each side until browned
  6. Once cooked, remove the steak from the pad an set to the side
  7. Drain the excess grease from from the pan turn the heat to medium low
  8. Pour the sauce into the pan and bring to a simmer stirring occasionally
  9. When the sauce is simmering, add the beef to the sauce and stir to combine
  10. Add 2 cups of butter lettuce and 1/2 cup of shredded cabbage to a salad bowl
  11. Add 4 ounces of flank steak on to the salad
  12. Garnish with sesame seeds and green onion
  13. Drizzle sauce from the pan over the salad
  14. Serve and enjoy!
